This paper deals with predicting links in complex networks with multiple types of interactions and complicated dependency structures between layers. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including social networks (cs.SOC), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures (cs.DS), and data mining (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of mutual information, which is a common technique in statistical inference and data analysis (cs.SD). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI, cs.SD, and cs.SOC, followed by cs.LG and cs.DS.
